@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Description"
@prev "Main"
@{u}Introduction@{uu}

The Thor filedatabase can be made to hold the complete Aminet @{"INDEX." link "FAQ" 0} Now this is
very useful as it allows you to search for files offline. @{"Sortmail" link "FAQ" 0} can be configured
to receive the @{"aminet-daily" link "FAQ" 0} or @{"aminet-weekly" link "FAQ" 0} mailing lists and parse them into the
database, therefore keeping you informed on new uploads via the newfiles window and
updating the filedatabase.

So what if you wanted to download a file you have found in the database or newfiles
window?

Well previously there has been a script (supplied with Thor) called ftpget.daftp.
This can be run after (multi)selecting files from the newfiles window and/or from
the file database window. The script would write these files to a batch file for
daFTP to process.

With Thor2.3+ there is now an easier way to do this :) When @{"enabled" link "FAQ" 0} Thor can now
create download events, similar to the way events are created for sending email and
news. Now clicking on a file in the newfiles window or the file database window, a
download event is automatically written.

OK, so now you have these download events, how can you download these files from
Aminet? This script provides a solution :)
@endnode

@node "Description" "Description"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Description"
@{u}Description@{uu}

ncFTPevents.br allows downloading of files from Aminet via selection from  the Thor
filedatabase. Download events can be selected from the  filedatabase window or from
the newfiles window which displays the  @{"aminet-daily" link "FAQ" 0} or @{"aminet-weekly" link "FAQ" 0} mailing list
files. 

ncFTP is used to fetch the files when online, which is part of the standard  AmiTCP
distribution.

An optional log file is written to your EMail conference to indicate success or
failure of the selected files. CPS figures are written to the log file. Optional
retries are allowed upon failure of an event.

Included is a script to @{"enableĀdownloadĀevents" link "FAQ" 0} in Thor 2.3+.

This script was written primarily to be included in an auto poll script so no user
interaction is required and Thor does not have to be running.  If Thor is found to
be running then notification upon completion is given using Thor's GUI.

Included in the documentation is information on how to parse and Aminet @{"INDEX" link "FAQ" 0} file
into the Thor filedatabase and how to subscribe to the Aminet Mailing List and parse
the @{"newfiles" link "FAQ" 0} into the Thor filedatabase.

ncFTPevents.br is freely distributable, but remains the copyright of Shaun Downend.

Any bugs or problems, then please @{"Email" link "Author" 0} me.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Description"
@{u}Installation@{uu}

Copy cfgtcp to Thor:s/cfgtcp. This modified script enables download events! It is
important that you @{b}@{fg shine}run this script@{ub}@{fg text} before you try to make download events in Thor.

Copy the arexx script to whereever you want, preferably Thor:Rexx/ or REXX:.

There are settings which need to be configured at the start of the arexx script:

bbs = "the name of your TCP system in Thor". e.g. "Internet" or "News&Mail"

conf = "the name of your email conference". This should be "EMail".

aminet = "the name of your nearest aminet mirror site".
         e.g. "src.doc.ic.ac.uk" is mine.
         @{b}NOTE@{ub} - if you like to download new files from the newfiles window
         then it is prudent to set this to "wuarchive.wustl.edu". This is
         because the aminet mailing list of new files is sent from here.
         The newly uploaded files may not have propagated to the other
         aminet mirrors but the time you try to download the files.

mainaminet = "the main aminet site" Ideally this should be set to
             "wuarchive.wustl.edu" or another full mirror. This site is
             used as a backup site when (new)files are not found at your
             local mirror.

downloaddir = "where you want the downloaded files to be stored". e.g.
              "Work:downloads/". Don't forget a trailing slash or colon!

ncftppath = Should normally be "AmiTCP:bin/".

logfile = "1" to enable a logfile, "0" to switch it off. The logfile is
          written as an email message in your configured system and conference.

retry = "1" for retries, and "0" for no retries. This switch will determine whether
        the event is marked as ERR when it fails.

trymain = "1" for automatic retry of failed events at the main aminet
          (mainaminet) site. "0" to turn off automatic retry of failed
          events.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "FAQ"
@prev "Installation"
@{u}Usage@{uu}

The arexx script can be run from a shell or from a button in DOpus, or even from
Thor.

No arguments are required but an optional command line argument exists to allow
selection of an alternative Aminet mirror.

Thor does not need to be running for this script to work. If Thor is found to be
running then notification upon completion is given using Thor's GUI.

Make sure you have altered the settings at the beginning of the arexx script to suit
your setup.

This script has been written so that it takes no user input. This is so that it can
be used in an auto poll script.

Note:- ncFTP can be terminated by activating the window and pressing CTRL-C.
@endnode

@node "FAQ" "FAQ"
@next "Legal Stuff"
@prev "Usage"
@{u}FAQ@{uu}

Q: How do I import the aminet INDEX into the Thor filedatabase?   

A: First you need to download the INDEX file from aminet. The index file can be
   found in aminets root dir - /pub/aminet/INDEX.
   Next you need to parse this file into the Thor filedatabase
   using an arexx script supplied with Thor called AddAminetFileList.br.
   Check out @{"Thor:docs/arexx.guide" link "Thor:Docs/Arexx.guide/main" 0} for more information on using
   this script.

Q: How do I subscribe to the aminet-daily or aminet-weekly mailing list?  

A: Send an email to <listproc@mail.wustl.edu>. The subject is unimportant.
   The body of the email message should contain one line:-

   subscribe aminet-daily your@email.address

   ...for a daily list of newfiles, or

   subscribe aminet-weekly your@email.address

   ...for a weekly newfiles list.

Q: How do I get Thor to add the files from the aminet mailing list to the Thor
   filedatabase? 

A: An arexx script SortMail.br exists to sort incoming email, e.g. mailing lists
   into separate conferences. It can also be used to parse an aminet-daily or
   aminet-weekly filelists into the filesdatabase. The last message is also
   displayed in the Thor newfiles window. You need to configure SortMail using
   CfgSortMail.thor. Check out @{"thor:docs/sortmail.guide" link "Thor:Docs/SortMail.guide/main" 0} for more information on
   setting up sortmail.

Q: How do you enable download events in Thor?

A: Install the modified cfgtcp in Thor:s/ and execute it before running Thor.
   Now download events should be enabled the next time you run Thor.
@endnode

