@node "History" "History"
@next "Updates"
@prev "Legal Stuff"
@{u}History@{uu}

v1.0  04/06/96 Internal testing. Not publically released.

v1.1  08/06/96 Fixed a bug with the arexx port parsing. Initial public release.

v1.2  12/06/96 Fixed a bug which may be caused by different versions of ncFTP.
               Added an optional retry switch (failed events are not marked as
               ERR)
               Changed the logfile format to that of an internal email message
               (This also works around the problems of using the scriptmsg
               facility).
               If Thor is already running the user is now informed of
               success/failure upon completion of the script.
               Not publically released.

v1.3  16/06/96 Many changes made to make the script more intelligent.
               When the logfile is enabled:-
                       Notification if AmiTCP is not running.
                       Notification if an incorrect ncFTP path is given.
                       Notification of failure to connect to aminet.
                       CPS figures are logged.
               Verification of downloaded files should now be foolproof.
               It reads info from the new temporary ncFTP log to see if the file
               was transferred @{b}fully@{ub}.
               When Thor is running it now updates the conference window if open.
               When Thor is running it now refreshes the email conference to show
               the new message @{b}@{i}if@{ub}@{ui} you are already in the email conference. No
               more selecting a different conference and back to email to see the
               new message :).
               Optional command line argument to change the default aminet mirror.
v1.31 19/06/96 Added verification of configured paths for the download directory
               and ncFTP path.
               Fixed many bugs in the validation of the FTP process :(
               Added code to handle the user terminating (CTRL C) the ncFTP
               process. Will now clean up and exit properly.
               Added support for different responses from servers when a
               file is not found. Tested on wuarchive.wustl.edu,
               ftp.aminet.org and src.doc.ic.ac.uk. I hope I have covered
               everything :)  

v1.32 23/06/96 Add automatic retry of failed events.
               The log message is only marked as important if there were errors.
               A new version of the Thor:s/cfgtcp script has been included. 
               It fixes problems with editing download events in the events 
               editor.
               Inclusion of a maintenance script, TidyDLEvents.br, by Neil 
               Bothwick.
@endnode

@node "Updates" "Updates"
@next "Credits"
@prev "History"
@{u}Updates@{uu}

I have no plans to develop this script too much further. This is only a temporary
solution. At some stage in the future Aminet downloads from Thor's filedatabase will
be controlled internally by Thor.

If you find any bugs then email me and I will fix them. If you want additional
features, or you come up with a good suggestion then email me  and I will try to see
if I can implement them. :-)
@endnode

